-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- tloz_oos.lua — game module for the Archipelago BizHawk connector.
--                The Legend of Zelda: Oracle of Seasons (Game Boy Color)
--
-- STATUS: location DETECTION + goal are REAL and SOURCE-DERIVED from the official
-- AP world worlds/tloz_oos (Client.py + data/locations.py + common/Util.py, the
-- `oos` branch of github.com/Dinopony/ArchipelagoOoS, world_version 21.0.0). The
-- 255-entry flag table + 16-entry Gasha counter list below were GENERATED by a
-- Python script that imports the real LOCATIONS_DATA and replicates, byte-for-byte:
--   • common/Util.py build_location_name_to_id_dict()  → the AP location id, which
--     for every flag location is literally  flag_byte*0x100 + bit_mask  (default
--     mask 0x20). There is NO separate base offset — the id IS the (byte,mask).
--   • the room→flag_byte fixup at the bottom of locations.py (chest-style
--     locations with no explicit flag_byte derive one from their room number).
--   • Client.py process_checked_locations() detection math + the deterministic
--     Gasha-Nut counter rule.
-- so the ids AND the detection bytes/masks are exact, not hand-copied. Loads
-- crash-free on any ROM; self-disables when the cartridge is not Oracle of Seasons.
--
-- MEMORY MODEL (BizHawk Game Boy Color — same as the LADX module)
-- ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
--   The OoS AP client (Client.py, a BizHawkClient) reads GBC memory through the
--   "System Bus" domain for everything except its two ROM-identity reads. We do
--   the same: all RAM addresses here are GB System-Bus addresses.
--     • Location check flags live in a 0x500-byte block at 0xC600..0xCB00 (one or
--       more bits per location). A check is "done" when
--         flag_bytes[flag_byte - 0xC600] & bit_mask == bit_mask
--       (Client.py uses `== bit_mask`, not `> 0`, so multi-bit masks like 0x60
--       require ALL their bits — replicated exactly).
--     • 16 deterministic "Gasha Nut #N" locations are NOT individual flag bits;
--       they are gated by a COUNTER:  count = flag_bytes[0xC649-0xC600] >> 2 ,
--       and the first `count` of the ordered Gasha ids are reported checked.
--     • game_state (0xC2EE) == 2 means the player is actually in-game.
--     • current_room = (0xCC49 << 8) | 0xCC4C  drives the goal.
--   ROM identity (the two ROM-domain reads the client uses):
--     • 0x0134 (9 bytes) = GB header title; an Oracle of Seasons cart reads
--       "ZELDA DIN" there (Ages reads "ZELDA NAYRU"). Used as the AP-cart gate.
--     • 0xFFFC0 (64 bytes) = AP-written slot name (the client's auth) — not needed
--       for detection, so not read here.
--
-- DETECTION GATE (mirrors Client.py game_watcher)
--   poll() reports a check only when game_state (0xC2EE) == 2 (the exact guard
--   `read_result[0][0] != 2: return` the client uses). The title screen / menus /
--   save-select frames read a different state, so they never report checks.
--
-- GOAL (mirrors Client.py process_game_completion — BOTH goal options)
--   • beat_onox  (slot_data goal == 0, the default): current_room == 0x0790
--     (the room with Din's descending crystal after Onox/Dragon Onox).
--   • beat_ganon (slot_data goal == 1, linked/Ganon ending): current_room ==
--     0x059A (Zelda lying down) AND flag 0xCA9A & 0x80 (Ganon beaten).
--   The module learns which goal applies from ctx.slot_data.goal when present; with
--   no slot_data it accepts EITHER completion condition (so a solo seed still
--   finishes), which can never false-positive — both are end-of-game rooms.
--
-- receive_item(): DOCUMENTED NO-OP. OoS items_handling = 0b001 — the PATCHED GAME
-- grants its own locally-found items, so a SOLO seed plays fully and every check is
-- reported in a multiworld. Delivering REMOTE multiworld items is the client's
-- guarded write path (it polls a received-item index at 0xC6A0, then writes the
-- next item's id/subid into the 2-byte struct at 0xCBFB ONLY when that struct is
-- empty AND the player is not inside Blaino's Gym — Blaino calls a writing player a
-- cheater). That write handshake is the one piece that needs in-emulator
-- verification before it is trusted, so it is GATED OFF here rather than shipped
-- unverified (a mistimed write could be rejected or corrupt the item struct).
-- Check reporting + goal are fully live regardless.
--
-- MODULE CONTRACT (called by bizhawk_ap_connector.lua)
--   M.init(ctx) / M.poll() -> {ids} / M.is_goal_complete() -> bool /
--   M.receive_item(item_id, meta)
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

